main event: USAF radar operators observed 2 or 3 unidentified targets near Wiesbaden, Germany on July 7, 1950.
interesting points: The radar detected the objects at an altitude of approximately 11,000 feet.,The unidentified objects moved at extremely high speeds of approximately 2,000 to 3,000 miles per hour.,The targets appeared to separate into 4 or 5 blurred individual targets.,The Wiesbaden control tower operator confirmed no jet aircraft were known to be in the area at that time.,An airman reported hearing sounds similar to low-flying jet aircraft around the same time as the radar observation.
witness description: USAF airman associated with the 1947th AACS Squadron
